1
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,500
Your daughter is here. Dad.

2
00:01:57,540 --> 00:01:58,099
You're back.

3
00:02:03,299 --> 00:02:04,099
Where's the cake?

4
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,239
Cake?

5
00:02:05,859 --> 00:02:07,180
Haven't I told you many times?

6
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:09,039
That stuff is deadly sweet, you should eat less of it.

7
00:02:09,539 --> 00:02:10,840
I can skip the cake.

8
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:13,240
But there should at least be a bouquet of flowers.

9
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:14,400
Flowers?

10
00:02:14,860 --> 00:02:16,000
You want to give them to Ms. Liu?

11
00:02:16,039 --> 00:02:16,900
I'll go buy them for you.

12
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,680
This time it's not for her.

13
00:02:20,020 --> 00:02:21,479
You have a new target?

14
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:23,560
You're playing dumb with me, aren't you?

15
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:24,740
I'm asking you.

16
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:26,139
What did you come here for?

17
00:02:26,539 --> 00:02:27,379
I just had nothing to do.

18
00:02:27,379 --> 00:02:28,560
So I came to see you.

19
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,400
I'm so mad.

20
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:36,840
Alright, are you really mad?

21
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:37,840
I know.

22
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:39,240
It's your birthday, right?

23
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,280
I bought you both the cake and flowers.

24
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,300
They'll be delivered in a bit.

25
00:02:43,099 --> 00:02:43,759
I knew it.

26
00:02:43,759 --> 00:02:45,199
My daughter wouldn't forget my birthday.

27
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:47,000
You really are a big kid.

28
00:02:49,340 --> 00:02:51,719
Alright, let's cut the cake.

29
00:02:54,780 --> 00:02:55,219
Dad.

30
00:02:55,419 --> 00:02:56,419
This first piece...

31
00:02:56,419 --> 00:02:57,379
You have the first one.

32
00:02:57,379 --> 00:02:58,219
No.

33
00:02:58,240 --> 00:02:59,300
This first piece...

34
00:02:59,360 --> 00:03:00,460
Must go to Ms. Liu.

35
00:03:00,460 --> 00:03:00,960
Give it to Ms. Liu.

36
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,620
No.

37
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:02,080
This is for me...

38
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:03,219
I'll eat a smaller piece.

39
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,240
This one is too big.

40
00:03:04,719 --> 00:03:06,659
That small one is for Xiao Fan later.

41
00:03:07,259 --> 00:03:08,020
Why?

42
00:03:08,539 --> 00:03:09,599
Really, this piece is too big.

43
00:03:09,599 --> 00:03:10,219
I... Take it.

44
00:03:10,219 --> 00:03:12,719
I can't eat this piece.

45
00:03:14,659 --> 00:03:15,360
The big piece is for me...

46
00:03:15,419 --> 00:03:15,919
I...

47
00:03:15,979 --> 00:03:17,099
I can eat it.

48
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:17,979
Gou'er Ye.

49
00:03:18,020 --> 00:03:18,919
You stepped on my foot.

50
00:03:19,639 --> 00:03:20,379
You stepped on my foot.

51
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:22,759
You're welcome.

52
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:23,680
You're welcome.

53
00:03:24,759 --> 00:03:27,139
No, the old gentleman is a bit confused.

54
00:03:27,139 --> 00:03:28,020
And hard of hearing.

55
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,379
Please don't hold it against him.

56
00:03:29,580 --> 00:03:29,979
Right.

57
00:03:30,240 --> 00:03:31,900
I won't hold it against you.

58
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:36,379
Birthday boy

59
00:03:36,599 --> 00:03:37,080
Quick

60
00:03:37,080 --> 00:03:37,599
Hurry up and cut it

61
00:03:37,599 --> 00:03:39,020
I haven't even gotten my tiny slice yet

62
00:03:39,419 --> 00:03:39,960
Hurry

63
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:41,479
Give it to Yang Dajie first

64
00:03:41,539 --> 00:03:42,900
The old lady is wiping her tears

65
00:03:44,180 --> 00:03:44,979
Yang Dajie

66
00:03:45,199 --> 00:03:45,860
Yang Dajie

67
00:03:46,039 --> 00:03:46,719
You have this piece

68
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:47,240
Here

69
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,139
Professor Zhu

70
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:49,219
What's going on?

71
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,620
Did you upset your wife?

72
00:03:50,780 --> 00:03:51,319
I...

73
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:52,800
I didn't

74
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:53,219
This...

75
00:03:53,479 --> 00:03:55,439
She's just a bit sad

76
00:03:56,479 --> 00:03:58,060
On such a happy occasion?

77
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:59,719
Why are you sad?

78
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:04,020
A child's birthday is the mother's day of hardship.

79
00:04:05,419 --> 00:04:06,139
Professor Zhu

80
00:04:06,539 --> 00:04:07,819
How can you take advantage of me?

81
00:04:09,319 --> 00:04:10,680
Boss Li, you misunderstood

82
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:12,180
I didn't take advantage of you

83
00:04:12,740 --> 00:04:14,360
My son's birthday...

84
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,979
...is on the same day as yours

85
00:04:16,180 --> 00:04:17,740
Still sounds like you're taking advantage of me

86
00:04:19,079 --> 00:04:20,680
Whenever this day comes around...

87
00:04:20,759 --> 00:04:22,060
...she misses our son

88
00:04:22,139 --> 00:04:23,180
And when she misses him...

89
00:04:23,240 --> 00:04:24,259
...she wipes away tears

90
00:04:24,339 --> 00:04:25,519
Let me say a few words

91
00:04:26,319 --> 00:04:28,579
Heaven and Earth are an inn for all things;

92
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:29,660
Time is...

93
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:31,379
...a traveler of all ages.

94
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:34,019
You should look past the matters of children

95
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,319
My condolences.

96
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,120
What nonsense are you spouting?

97
00:04:38,279 --> 00:04:39,399
Everything is fine...

98
00:04:39,399 --> 00:04:41,100
...and you talk as if my son is dead

99
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:41,779
Well...

100
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,579
Then why is she crying like that?

101
00:04:45,019 --> 00:04:47,680
My son hasn't visited us in over half a year

102
00:04:48,959 --> 00:04:49,660
Is he in jail?

103
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:51,240
Old Fan

104
00:04:51,519 --> 00:04:52,980
You're a bit muddled today

105
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:56,060
Her son must be too busy with work to come

106
00:04:56,160 --> 00:04:57,600
Unlike my daughter

107
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,019
She visits me every couple of days

108
00:04:59,079 --> 00:04:59,980
She never gets tired of it

109
00:05:00,060 --> 00:05:00,819
Dad

110
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:02,019
Fan'ersai again

111
00:05:02,639 --> 00:05:04,220
You say my son doesn't come...

112
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:05,379
...and the daughter doesn't come either

113
00:05:06,019 --> 00:05:06,920
Look at me

114
00:05:07,060 --> 00:05:08,120
A son and a daughter...

115
00:05:08,339 --> 00:05:09,420
...raised for nothing

116
00:05:09,639 --> 00:05:10,879
You want them to come see you?

117
00:05:11,560 --> 00:05:12,259
That's easy

118
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,720
Just say you have a terminal illness

119
00:05:14,779 --> 00:05:15,579
You're critically ill

120
00:05:15,779 --> 00:05:16,600
They'll definitely come

121
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:16,959
No

122
00:05:16,959 --> 00:05:18,199
What kind of idea is that?

123
00:05:18,199 --> 00:05:19,160
Aren't you cursing them?

124
00:05:19,160 --> 00:05:20,079
Yeah, exactly

125
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,819
Saying they're critically ill will make them come?

126
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:24,519
You have to say a critical condition notice was issued

127
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:28,100
Now that is cursing them

128
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:30,220
What critical condition notice?

129
00:05:30,319 --> 00:05:32,379
You have to mention making a will

130
00:05:34,019 --> 00:05:35,199
Let me tell you, kids these days...

131
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:36,480
...are eyeing your assets

132
00:05:36,519 --> 00:05:38,060
Once you mention the will...

133
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:38,839
...they'll be here instantly

134
00:05:40,019 --> 00:05:40,420
This...

135
00:05:40,459 --> 00:05:41,060
This won't do

136
00:05:41,180 --> 00:05:41,579
Right

137
00:05:41,579 --> 00:05:42,439
That's just nonsense

138
00:05:42,439 --> 00:05:42,980
Right

139
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,060
Don't listen to any of them

140
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:47,300
Boss Li, what's your brilliant idea?

141
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:48,079
My opinion is...

142
00:05:49,279 --> 00:05:50,180
...you two...

143
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,139
...should just get a divorce

144
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:55,420
What are you saying?

145
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:57,819
It's not like I'm asking you to really divorce.

146
00:05:58,379 --> 00:05:59,160
What are you worried about?

147
00:05:59,819 --> 00:06:00,800
Listen to me.

148
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:03,060
Hurry up and take the toiletries

149
00:06:03,060 --> 00:06:04,279
and the laundry

150
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,279
out of the room.

151
00:06:05,579 --> 00:06:06,480
What is this for?

152
00:06:06,939 --> 00:06:07,860
Separation!

153
00:06:09,139 --> 00:06:10,759
If you're going to fake it, you have to make it look real.

154
00:06:11,540 --> 00:06:12,180
Yang Dajie,

155
00:06:12,779 --> 00:06:13,720
you just stay...

156
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:15,740
...stay in your room.

157
00:06:16,939 --> 00:06:17,879
Then where do I stay?

158
00:06:18,079 --> 00:06:18,819
You don't need to move.

159
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:21,319
Ms. Liu...

160
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,740
...Ms. Liu moves to Longevity Residence...

161
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:24,720
...to Professor Zhu's room.

162
00:06:25,019 --> 00:06:25,480
Me?

163
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,120
Then I...

164
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:27,079
You...

165
00:06:27,079 --> 00:06:28,079
...go to our place.

166
00:06:28,139 --> 00:06:29,240
You live with Professor Fan.

167
00:06:29,579 --> 00:06:30,860
I live with him?

168
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:31,399
Right. Look...

169
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,220
Then where will you stay?

170
00:06:33,259 --> 00:06:34,699
I'll move to Longevity Residence, to your place.

171
00:06:35,100 --> 00:06:35,839
Just making do.

172
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:38,480
You and Ms. Liu?

173
00:06:38,819 --> 00:06:40,879
No way, that's not appropriate.

174
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:43,240
Aren't you afraid of people gossiping?

175
00:06:43,779 --> 00:06:44,519
Isn't this for...

176
00:06:44,519 --> 00:06:46,779
...Professor Zhu's family reunion?

177
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:47,839
Public gossip...

178
00:06:47,899 --> 00:06:48,540
...I can handle it.

179
00:06:48,759 --> 00:06:49,439
I'm going all out.

180
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,379
You're going all out?

181
00:06:51,459 --> 00:06:53,040
Is Ms. Liu willing?

182
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,720
We'll work on her together.

183
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,259
Grandpa Zhu, Grandma Yang.

184
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,579
These two...

185
00:06:57,660 --> 00:06:58,680
...say they are looking for you.

186
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,379
It's my son and daughter.

187
00:07:02,079 --> 00:07:03,480
You really came.

188
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,660
Of course we came.

189
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:05,920
We heard you two are divorcing.

190
00:07:06,819 --> 00:07:07,720
Getting a divorce.

191
00:07:07,920 --> 00:07:08,500
This...

192
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:09,480
We took time off to come.

193
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,540
What is going on here?

194
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:11,420
Exactly.

195
00:07:11,439 --> 00:07:11,959
This...

196
00:07:12,079 --> 00:07:13,279
Seeing you two like this...

197
00:07:13,339 --> 00:07:14,240
...you won't be able to divorce.

198
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:15,120
We are relieved.

199
00:07:15,319 --> 00:07:15,680
Well...

200
00:07:15,759 --> 00:07:17,319
Who says we can't divorce?

201
00:07:17,319 --> 00:07:18,560
We are divorcing right now.

202
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:21,000
But you look so loving.

203
00:07:21,000 --> 00:07:22,480
It doesn't look like you're divorcing.

204
00:07:23,019 --> 00:07:23,519
This...

205
00:07:23,620 --> 00:07:24,240
This is...

206
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:25,680
What loving?

207
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,560
You stay away from me.

208
00:07:27,180 --> 00:07:27,819
Old Zhu!

209
00:07:28,939 --> 00:07:29,920
Fine, I'll stay away.

210
00:07:30,480 --> 00:07:31,740
Who wants to be near you?

211
00:07:31,779 --> 00:07:32,600
It's a good thing.

212
00:07:33,879 --> 00:07:34,459
Children.

213
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,240
Good thing.

214
00:07:36,220 --> 00:07:38,879
Your parents have been at odds for decades.

215
00:07:39,139 --> 00:07:40,639
Now they are finally free.

216
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,240
You should be happy for your parents.

217
00:07:43,560 --> 00:07:44,379
Who are you?

218
00:07:45,279 --> 00:07:46,339
My parents' business...

219
00:07:46,420 --> 00:07:47,620
...you stirred it up, didn't you?

220
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,319
Yes.

221
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:49,540
No, I didn't.

222
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:50,220
I didn't.

223
00:07:51,139 --> 00:07:51,639
No.

224
00:07:52,399 --> 00:07:53,160
Dad, Mom.

225
00:07:53,160 --> 00:07:53,879
Let's not talk here.

226
00:07:53,879 --> 00:07:54,579
There are outsiders.

227
00:07:54,579 --> 00:07:55,420
Let's go back to the room.

228
00:07:55,420 --> 00:07:56,879
Which room?

229
00:07:57,379 --> 00:07:58,959
They are separated.

230
00:08:02,339 --> 00:08:02,939
Mom,

231
00:08:03,579 --> 00:08:04,980
even if you really want a divorce,

232
00:08:05,139 --> 00:08:07,019
you still need a valid reason, right?

233
00:08:07,300 --> 00:08:08,060
A reason?

234
00:08:09,100 --> 00:08:11,300
The reason is just that lately you guys...

235
00:08:13,319 --> 00:08:14,519
haven't agreed on one yet.

236
00:08:15,180 --> 00:08:17,259
Is this something you discuss on the spot?

237
00:08:18,259 --> 00:08:18,899
By the way,

238
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:21,160
how are things with your husband lately?

239
00:08:21,180 --> 00:08:21,939
Still fighting?

240
00:08:21,939 --> 00:08:23,540
We fight. How could we not?

241
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,699
Every day. You know his temper.

242
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:27,860
You've gained weight recently.

243
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:27,939
You've really gained weight.

244
00:08:28,459 --> 00:08:29,360
Let me tell you,

245
00:08:29,439 --> 00:08:31,240
you really need to drink less.

246
00:08:31,439 --> 00:08:32,779
Don't drive after drinking.

247
00:08:33,299 --> 00:08:34,639
It'd be best to quit smoking too.

248
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:35,679
Smoking?

249
00:08:35,879 --> 00:08:37,500
I don't really smoke much anymore.

250
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:38,279
Wait, no.

251
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,679
Why are we talking about this?

252
00:08:40,360 --> 00:08:41,639
Between husband and wife,

253
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:43,779
there should be mutual respect and understanding.

254
00:08:44,539 --> 00:08:45,519
You can't be too particular.

255
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:48,000
You can't just threaten divorce at the drop of a hat.

256
00:08:49,759 --> 00:08:50,399
Dad,

257
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,460
don't you understand this perfectly well?

258
00:08:52,860 --> 00:08:55,080
Then why are you divorcing Mom?

259
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:58,220
I'm teaching you by example here.

260
00:08:58,480 --> 00:09:00,720
I want to be a negative example for you.

261
00:09:01,039 --> 00:09:02,259
Never heard of that.

262
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,240
The two of us...

263
00:09:03,600 --> 00:09:04,559
plan to divorce.

264
00:09:04,559 --> 00:09:05,039
But,

265
00:09:05,080 --> 00:09:06,840
if you two come visit, we...

266
00:09:07,440 --> 00:09:08,559
might not divorce after all.

267
00:09:09,899 --> 00:09:11,419
Are you two just messing around?

268
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,759
If you don't give me...

269
00:09:12,759 --> 00:09:14,299
the real reason for the divorce today,

270
00:09:15,539 --> 00:09:16,480
my brother and I...

271
00:09:17,519 --> 00:09:19,240
my brother and I will come every day.

272
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:20,759
Every day?

273
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:24,019
That would be too annoying.

274
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:31,539
How about that?

275
00:09:32,179 --> 00:09:33,200
My trick worked, didn't it?

276
00:09:33,899 --> 00:09:35,080
Alright. Is it useful?

277
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:36,899
Maybe he'll even come today.

278
00:09:36,919 --> 00:09:37,659
Really?

279
00:09:38,179 --> 00:09:39,139
Come.

280
00:09:41,659 --> 00:09:42,720
Dad, Mom.

281
00:09:43,360 --> 00:09:44,120
Today,

282
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,460
Sis and I have discussed it.

283
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:47,440
We must solve this problem for you two.

284
00:09:47,899 --> 00:09:48,860
No need.

285
00:09:49,860 --> 00:09:51,379
Your mom and I...

286
00:09:51,679 --> 00:09:52,960
have reached an agreement.

287
00:09:54,000 --> 00:09:54,519
Divorce.

288
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,259
We are definitely divorcing.

289
00:09:58,059 --> 00:09:59,480
Wait... did you talk him into this again?

290
00:10:00,299 --> 00:10:00,720
I...

291
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:02,379
What did I do?

292
00:10:04,799 --> 00:10:05,379
You guys talk.

293
00:10:06,159 --> 00:10:06,700
You guys talk.

294
00:10:08,259 --> 00:10:08,820
You guys talk.

295
00:10:12,620 --> 00:10:13,299
Dad

296
00:10:13,620 --> 00:10:14,480
Sit down.

297
00:10:15,419 --> 00:10:16,679
What's going on?

298
00:10:17,159 --> 00:10:18,220
But you and Mom have been together...

299
00:10:18,220 --> 00:10:19,480
...living together for decades...

300
00:10:19,659 --> 00:10:21,179
...and raised the two of us...

301
00:10:21,259 --> 00:10:22,299
...relatively outstanding children.

302
00:10:22,299 --> 00:10:22,820
Exactly.

303
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:24,379
How is it possible there's not a shred of affection...

304
00:10:24,379 --> 00:10:25,440
...left at all?

305
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,600
Our affection...

306
00:10:26,679 --> 00:10:27,820
...came to an end long ago.

307
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,620
What do you mean "came to an end"?

308
00:10:29,620 --> 00:10:30,679
Well, we...

309
00:10:31,059 --> 00:10:31,519
We...

310
00:10:31,519 --> 00:10:33,299
When did we ever have affection?

311
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,460
We did...

312
00:10:35,340 --> 00:10:36,039
...yeah right!

313
00:10:36,379 --> 00:10:37,059
To be honest with you...

314
00:10:37,139 --> 00:10:38,399
...I've been sick of it for ages.

315
00:10:38,519 --> 00:10:40,120
Then let me tell you the truth.

316
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:41,840
I've had enough of her for a long time.

317
00:10:42,179 --> 00:10:44,120
He's always been rude and crude.

318
00:10:44,299 --> 00:10:46,419
She's always been petty and calculating.

319
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,340
After I got married...

320
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,720
...I regretted it immensely.

321
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:50,039
Before I got married...

322
00:10:50,039 --> 00:10:51,299
...I almost threw myself on the tracks.

323
00:10:51,779 --> 00:10:52,740
Now I've figured it out.

324
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,019
Better a short pain than a long one.

325
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:55,379
Now I finally understand.

326
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,720
Better to divorce sooner than later.

327
00:10:57,659 --> 00:10:58,179
Dad.

328
00:10:59,340 --> 00:10:59,940
Mom.

329
00:11:00,980 --> 00:11:01,460
No...

330
00:11:01,840 --> 00:11:03,139
When did you two...

331
00:11:03,220 --> 00:11:04,740
...become like this?

332
00:11:04,840 --> 00:11:06,419
Actually, we haven't changed.

333
00:11:06,519 --> 00:11:07,139
Well...

334
00:11:07,139 --> 00:11:08,340
Dad is still a good dad.

335
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,019
And Mom is still a good mom.

336
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:10,799
It's a pity...

337
00:11:11,120 --> 00:11:12,360
...we're just not a good couple.

338
00:11:13,559 --> 00:11:14,200
So...

339
00:11:14,700 --> 00:11:15,820
We are definitely divorcing.

340
00:11:16,559 --> 00:11:17,240
Absolutely divorcing.

341
00:11:17,779 --> 00:11:18,559
We have to divorce.

342
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,700
And we must divorce immediately.

343
00:11:20,799 --> 00:11:22,320
Hurry up and divorce, the sooner the better.

344
00:11:24,240 --> 00:11:24,679
Dad.

345
00:11:25,019 --> 00:11:25,460
Mom.

346
00:11:26,120 --> 00:11:27,860
If you insist on getting a divorce...

347
00:11:28,059 --> 00:11:29,720
...then don't blame us siblings...

348
00:11:30,559 --> 00:11:31,419
...for agreeing.

349
00:11:31,539 --> 00:11:33,460
I don't care if you agree or not...

350
00:11:33,539 --> 00:11:34,419
There's...

351
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:35,039
What?

352
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:36,480
You agreed?

353
00:11:37,299 --> 00:11:38,279
If breaking up...

354
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,740
...can relieve you two of your pain quickly...

355
00:11:41,340 --> 00:11:43,419
...then why would we object?

356
00:11:44,220 --> 00:11:44,820
Dad.

357
00:11:45,720 --> 00:11:46,279
Mom.

358
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:48,000
Actually, we...

359
00:11:48,419 --> 00:11:49,720
...also have to thank you two.

360
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,120
For the sake of this family...

361
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,600
...and for the two of us...

362
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:54,559
...you lived together in pain for so many years.

363
00:11:54,559 --> 00:11:55,019
Actually...

364
00:11:56,299 --> 00:11:56,980
Dad, Mom.

365
00:11:57,460 --> 00:11:58,159
Thank you.

366
00:11:58,440 --> 00:11:58,919
Thanks.

367
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,019
In the past...

368
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:02,100
...we didn't do well.

369
00:12:03,320 --> 00:12:04,299
Because we were busy with work...

370
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:05,580
...and didn't visit you often.

371
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:07,340
Thinking about it now...

372
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:09,039
...we really regret it deeply.

373
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,840
Even though you two are divorced...

374
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:14,299
...you are still our dearest Mom and Dad.

375
00:12:14,559 --> 00:12:15,480
From now on...

376
00:12:15,559 --> 00:12:16,240
The two of us...

377
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,340
Is every week okay?

378
00:12:17,399 --> 00:12:18,779
We'll come to see you every week.

379
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:19,440
We promise.

380
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:19,980
We promise.

381
00:12:20,500 --> 00:12:22,000
If that's the case...

382
00:12:23,639 --> 00:12:24,379
Then, Old Zhu...

383
00:12:24,899 --> 00:12:25,840
...should we still divorce?

384
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:30,259
If that's the case...

385
00:12:32,220 --> 00:12:33,340
Let me tell you the truth.

386
00:12:33,659 --> 00:12:35,580
We were joking with you.

387
00:12:39,960 --> 00:12:41,039
But you coming to see us often...

388
00:12:41,039 --> 00:12:42,200
...that can't change.

389
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,159
They're having a family reunion.

390
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,139
What's wrong with you now?

391
00:12:51,919 --> 00:12:55,379
Watching their whole family go out for a reunion dinner,

392
00:12:55,740 --> 00:12:57,879
how can I not feel bad?

393
00:12:59,220 --> 00:13:00,720
It's just a meal, isn't it?

394
00:13:01,559 --> 00:13:03,000
So what if they didn't invite you?

395
00:13:04,019 --> 00:13:06,179
Their family reunion was my brilliant idea,

396
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:07,899
and they didn't invite me either.

397
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:09,779
Aside from swallowing my saliva,

398
00:13:09,860 --> 00:13:11,000
I haven't said anything, have I?

399
00:13:11,919 --> 00:13:13,879
It's not about the meal.

400
00:13:14,720 --> 00:13:16,440
It's seeing them

401
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:19,860
all happy and together.

402
00:13:20,179 --> 00:13:22,039
It makes me think of my...

403
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:24,639
son who married a wife and forgot his mother,

404
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:25,820
that rotten son.

405
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,679
I get it.

406
00:13:28,100 --> 00:13:29,080
You're envious.

407
00:13:29,259 --> 00:13:30,779
Who's envious?

408
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:32,820
I'm jealous.

409
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:35,220
Boss Li,

410
00:13:35,659 --> 00:13:37,460
come up with a brilliant plan for me too.

411
00:13:37,700 --> 00:13:39,500
Make my son come visit me.

412
00:13:40,059 --> 00:13:42,200
Ideally, bring my little grandson along.

413
00:13:42,299 --> 00:13:43,379
What's so hard about that?

414
00:13:44,659 --> 00:13:45,559
You fake a divorce too.

415
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:48,759
Who would I divorce?

416
00:13:48,940 --> 00:13:50,320
I'm all alone.

417
00:13:51,860 --> 00:13:53,320
How could I forget that?

418
00:13:53,679 --> 00:13:54,279
Honestly.

419
00:13:55,419 --> 00:13:56,419
But that doesn't matter.

420
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:58,940
Let's...

421
00:14:01,820 --> 00:14:02,980
stage a fake marriage.

422
00:14:04,940 --> 00:14:06,360
You mean let me...

423
00:14:07,039 --> 00:14:09,940
remarry and take another step forward?

424
00:14:10,519 --> 00:14:11,919
This idea...

425
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,299
that's a bit embarrassing.

426
00:14:14,460 --> 00:14:16,019
What's embarrassing about it?

427
00:14:16,259 --> 00:14:17,919
Isn't it to get your son to visit you?

428
00:14:18,139 --> 00:14:19,840
He must bring my grandson. Right.

429
00:14:21,580 --> 00:14:22,860
I'll go for it.

430
00:14:24,399 --> 00:14:25,340
Exactly.

431
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,779
It's too much trouble for you.

432
00:14:26,860 --> 00:14:27,539
It's the right thing to do.

433
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:30,179
What do you mean?

434
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:31,820
You mean...

435
00:14:32,899 --> 00:14:33,580
Me?

436
00:14:34,399 --> 00:14:35,620
Didn't you just say,

437
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:37,519
"Let's stage a fake marriage"?

438
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,620
No, I meant *you* stage a fake marriage.

439
00:14:39,759 --> 00:14:41,720
But I didn't say with me!

440
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:43,379
Don't be so polite.

441
00:14:43,379 --> 00:14:44,320
It's settled then.

442
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,000
I'm not being polite!

443
00:14:46,159 --> 00:14:47,820
We're not a good match!

444
00:14:48,500 --> 00:14:49,580
Isn't it fake?

445
00:14:49,580 --> 00:14:50,620
I can make do.

446
00:14:50,879 --> 00:14:52,440
How is it you "making do" with me?

447
00:14:52,759 --> 00:14:53,679
What do you mean?

448
00:14:53,980 --> 00:14:55,120
You look down on me?

449
00:14:55,159 --> 00:14:55,899
That's not it.

450
00:14:57,480 --> 00:14:58,740
It's not that I look down on you.

451
00:14:59,799 --> 00:15:01,860
Don't I already have someone in my heart?

452
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:04,220
It's fake anyway.

453
00:15:04,259 --> 00:15:06,200
I won't fight with her out of jealousy.

454
00:15:06,200 --> 00:15:07,740
It's no good if word gets out.

455
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:08,720
I'm afraid.

456
00:15:08,759 --> 00:15:10,500
I'm not afraid, so what are you afraid of?

457
00:15:10,500 --> 00:15:11,600
No, I mean...

458
00:15:11,899 --> 00:15:14,899
there are handsome old men younger and cooler than me

459
00:15:14,960 --> 00:15:16,000
wandering all over the community.

460
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,639
It doesn't have to be me.

461
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:18,659
For example...

462
00:15:20,200 --> 00:15:21,220
Xiao Fan.

463
00:15:21,299 --> 00:15:22,000
Professor Fan.

464
00:15:22,759 --> 00:15:23,620
Professor Fan?

465
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:24,940
Would he agree?

466
00:15:25,559 --> 00:15:27,019
That's a good idea.

467
00:15:27,860 --> 00:15:29,399
If your son hears you're getting married,

468
00:15:29,500 --> 00:15:30,759
he'll definitely rush over immediately.

469
00:15:30,960 --> 00:15:31,639
Right.

470
00:15:31,860 --> 00:15:33,320
The idea is good.

471
00:15:33,379 --> 00:15:36,039
But where do I find a fiancé?

472
00:15:36,039 --> 00:15:36,740
Right.

473
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:38,419
What's so hard about that?

474
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:39,960
Cai Ayi,

475
00:15:40,299 --> 00:15:41,700
if you don't mind,

476
00:15:41,759 --> 00:15:43,059
just hand this task over to...

477
00:15:43,519 --> 00:15:44,139
Boss Li.

478
00:15:47,039 --> 00:15:48,100
If we're going to pretend,

479
00:15:48,399 --> 00:15:49,960
we have to make them believe it.

480
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:51,379
So I think

481
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:52,879
you two are a better match.

482
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:53,659
No.

483
00:15:53,740 --> 00:15:54,279
Boss Li,

484
00:15:54,539 --> 00:15:56,500
you two are the real perfect match.

485
00:15:56,500 --> 00:15:58,220
Simply a match made in heaven.

486
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,860
Don't be so polite, you two.

487
00:16:01,059 --> 00:16:03,480
He is a big professor at a top university.

488
00:16:03,700 --> 00:16:05,220
His qualifications are better than mine.

489
00:16:05,639 --> 00:16:06,679
You are from a big private company,

490
00:16:06,679 --> 00:16:08,279
a retired former executive.

491
00:16:08,279 --> 00:16:09,519
Your benefits are better than mine.

492
00:16:09,860 --> 00:16:11,620
My physical condition is poor.

493
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:12,779
I have high blood pressure.

494
00:16:12,779 --> 00:16:14,360
My health isn't great either.

495
00:16:14,360 --> 00:16:15,500
I have low blood sugar.

496
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:16,980
I have a really bad temper.

497
00:16:17,399 --> 00:16:18,740
I'm narrow-minded.

498
00:16:19,059 --> 00:16:21,559
But your education is much better than mine.

499
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,860
I'm just a fake professor.

500
00:16:24,220 --> 00:16:26,620
My title of Boss was just nominal.

501
00:16:26,620 --> 00:16:28,500
Like a nanny holding a baby—it wasn't mine.

502
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:29,320
Well,

503
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:30,700
whatever official titles,

504
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:31,879
whatever positions,

505
00:16:31,879 --> 00:16:32,700
none of that matters.

506
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,779
What matters is having real knowledge.

507
00:16:34,899 --> 00:16:35,600
Exactly.

508
00:16:35,700 --> 00:16:36,980
So, compared to Professor Fan,

509
00:16:36,980 --> 00:16:38,480
I'm basically illiterate.

510
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:39,240
If you're illiterate,

511
00:16:39,240 --> 00:16:39,980
then I'm even more illiterate.

512
00:16:39,980 --> 00:16:41,799
I am the illiterate one.

513
00:16:41,919 --> 00:16:42,519
Gentlemen,

514
00:16:43,159 --> 00:16:44,419
what are you arguing about?

515
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,940
Has the fiancé candidate been decided?

516
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:47,679
Well,

517
00:16:47,899 --> 00:16:49,000
just for this spot,

518
00:16:49,059 --> 00:16:51,000
these two are arguing until they're red in the face.

519
00:16:52,620 --> 00:16:53,379
Gentlemen,

520
00:16:53,860 --> 00:16:54,580
how about this.

521
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,759
Cai Ayi is my roommate,

522
00:16:57,139 --> 00:16:58,639
and my good friend.

523
00:16:58,639 --> 00:16:58,980
Yes.

524
00:16:59,059 --> 00:17:00,720
Her business is my business.

525
00:17:00,779 --> 00:17:02,419
Helping her is helping me.

526
00:17:03,320 --> 00:17:03,980
Boss Li,

527
00:17:05,019 --> 00:17:06,019
this opportunity,

528
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:06,819
you...

529
00:17:07,519 --> 00:17:08,920
just let Professor Fan have it.

530
00:17:18,539 --> 00:17:19,779
Do we really have to dance?

531
00:17:19,819 --> 00:17:21,640
You must. Dance properly.

532
00:17:23,099 --> 00:17:24,480
Her son and daughter-in-law will be here soon.

533
00:17:25,259 --> 00:17:26,039
Hold her tighter.

534
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,160
Smile.

535
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:28,859
No cutting corners.

536
00:17:31,539 --> 00:17:32,240
Are you wrestling?

537
00:17:36,779 --> 00:17:38,039
Let go!

538
00:17:39,539 --> 00:17:40,900
What are you doing, old man?

539
00:17:40,980 --> 00:17:42,619
Holding my mom so tight.

540
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,180
Child, don't get upset yet.

541
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,740
How can I not be upset?

542
00:17:45,740 --> 00:17:47,259
It's not you he's holding.

543
00:17:47,799 --> 00:17:48,599
It's not your mom.

544
00:17:48,640 --> 00:17:49,519
Watch your language.

545
00:17:49,599 --> 00:17:50,420
I told you to calm down, now you're upsetting me!

546
00:17:50,420 --> 00:17:51,859
Mom, you too.

547
00:17:51,940 --> 00:17:53,640
You've been a widow for so many years.

548
00:17:53,759 --> 00:17:55,180
Why, at your age,

549
00:17:55,279 --> 00:17:57,359
are you pulling a stunt like this?

550
00:18:03,299 --> 00:18:05,319
Don't talk to me about remarriage yet

551
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:06,220
I'm asking you

552
00:18:06,839 --> 00:18:09,140
Why haven't you visited me for so long?

553
00:18:10,039 --> 00:18:11,099
You finally made it here

554
00:18:11,180 --> 00:18:13,480
Why didn't you bring my precious grandson?

555
00:18:13,599 --> 00:18:14,240
Mom

556
00:18:14,359 --> 00:18:16,839
Stop bringing up your precious grandson

557
00:18:16,940 --> 00:18:18,420
If you go and get remarried

558
00:18:18,559 --> 00:18:21,180
Whether you'll ever see your grandson again

559
00:18:21,359 --> 00:18:22,619
Is not even certain

560
00:18:23,839 --> 00:18:24,680
Why is that?

561
00:18:24,799 --> 00:18:26,000
My wife said

562
00:18:26,099 --> 00:18:26,740
Doudou

563
00:18:26,859 --> 00:18:28,039
Grandma doesn't want you anymore

564
00:18:28,099 --> 00:18:29,799
She went to be someone else's grandma

565
00:18:29,960 --> 00:18:31,700
Isn't that just total nonsense?

566
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,480
My wife also said

567
00:18:33,559 --> 00:18:35,460
If you're dead set on remarrying

568
00:18:35,539 --> 00:18:37,019
We can't stop you

569
00:18:37,420 --> 00:18:39,480
As the saying goes

570
00:18:39,559 --> 00:18:40,759
A grown daughter can't be kept at home

571
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,339
It's a grown mother can't be kept at home

572
00:18:43,380 --> 00:18:44,880
Keeping her breeds bad blood

573
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:45,880
Mom

574
00:18:46,359 --> 00:18:47,559
If you want to remarry

575
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:48,660
We won't stand in your way

576
00:18:48,740 --> 00:18:49,380
But, well

577
00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:51,119
You have to clear out of our old house

578
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:52,619
And hand it over to us

579
00:18:53,019 --> 00:18:54,039
Why on earth?

580
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:55,119
Mom

581
00:18:55,180 --> 00:18:56,640
This is also what my wife said

582
00:18:56,819 --> 00:18:57,420
Mom, you tell me

583
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,680
Since you're married off

584
00:18:58,759 --> 00:19:00,500
You should move into your in-laws'

585
00:19:00,619 --> 00:19:02,059
You keep mooching off your maiden home

586
00:19:02,140 --> 00:19:03,339
What does that look like?

587
00:19:04,660 --> 00:19:05,980
My wife also said

588
00:19:06,059 --> 00:19:07,039
Saying that...

589
00:19:07,119 --> 00:19:08,240
A married...

590
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:09,720
Mother...

591
00:19:09,779 --> 00:19:11,079
Is like spilled water

592
00:19:11,079 --> 00:19:12,420
Shut your mouth

593
00:19:12,839 --> 00:19:14,480
"My wife" this, "my wife" that

594
00:19:14,539 --> 00:19:16,440
Are you even my own son?

595
00:19:16,779 --> 00:19:18,140
Mom, I'm just relaying

596
00:19:18,140 --> 00:19:19,319
It's not what I mean

597
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:20,220
Still talking?

598
00:19:21,319 --> 00:19:22,839
You want to marry my mother-in-law

599
00:19:23,420 --> 00:19:24,259
Fine

600
00:19:25,099 --> 00:19:26,539
However

601
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:28,240
You must first sign a...

602
00:19:28,299 --> 00:19:30,160
Prenuptial property notarization

603
00:19:30,700 --> 00:19:32,940
I only have two properties and a car

604
00:19:33,339 --> 00:19:34,799
Savings are just a few million

605
00:19:35,059 --> 00:19:36,039
Do I still need a notary?

606
00:19:39,339 --> 00:19:40,839
That's quite a bit

607
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:42,259
No

608
00:19:42,500 --> 00:19:44,279
I mean...

609
00:19:44,480 --> 00:19:45,779
If you don't notarize

610
00:19:46,200 --> 00:19:48,859
Will your kids from before agree?

611
00:19:50,640 --> 00:19:52,480
I've never been married

612
00:19:52,759 --> 00:19:54,099
Where would I get kids from a previous marriage?

613
00:19:54,099 --> 00:19:55,099
You're hilarious

614
00:19:55,579 --> 00:19:57,400
No children?

615
00:19:58,140 --> 00:19:59,440
That's wonderful

616
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:02,960
So unfortunate

617
00:20:06,019 --> 00:20:07,039
My dear Dad

618
00:20:08,259 --> 00:20:09,220
Just like that, I'm a dad

619
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:11,759
Wha...

620
00:20:11,759 --> 00:20:12,400
What is it?

621
00:20:12,859 --> 00:20:14,640
It means before getting married

622
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:15,339
Write it down

623
00:20:15,460 --> 00:20:17,420
Whose assets go to which family

624
00:20:17,519 --> 00:20:18,400
When you die

625
00:20:18,400 --> 00:20:18,819
No

626
00:20:18,819 --> 00:20:19,160
When

627
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:19,779
When

628
00:20:19,819 --> 00:20:20,980
After you pass on

629
00:20:21,059 --> 00:20:23,019
Whose inheritance, whose children...

630
00:20:23,079 --> 00:20:23,920
Will inherit

631
00:20:25,420 --> 00:20:28,220
You beat around the bush just for my inheritance

632
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:30,319
Then let me tell you straight

633
00:20:31,140 --> 00:20:33,759
I won't do that whatever-certificate

634
00:20:34,579 --> 00:20:34,940
Mom

635
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,180
We can skip that whatever-notarization

636
00:20:37,900 --> 00:20:38,619
But you...

637
00:20:38,720 --> 00:20:41,099
Need to make a will for us first

638
00:20:41,099 --> 00:20:42,140
Then... Pfft!

639
00:20:44,099 --> 00:20:45,440
As soon as the will is done

640
00:20:45,559 --> 00:20:47,200
You'll play that game on me

641
00:20:47,240 --> 00:20:49,039
"Dalang, it's time for your medicine"

642
00:20:49,339 --> 00:20:50,500
Save it

643
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:51,539
I'm so angry

644
00:20:51,559 --> 00:20:52,759
Impossible, how could we do that?

645
00:20:52,759 --> 00:20:53,359
Dabao

646
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:58,400
You good-for-nothing.

647
00:20:58,500 --> 00:20:59,740
Why did you make Mom angry?

648
00:20:59,779 --> 00:21:01,480
Why is it my fault?

649
00:21:01,480 --> 00:21:02,480
You were the one who said it all.

650
00:21:02,480 --> 00:21:03,099
Shut up.

651
00:21:06,779 --> 00:21:07,359
Mom.

652
00:21:07,920 --> 00:21:09,599
Dabao is your own flesh and blood.

653
00:21:09,680 --> 00:21:10,680
Don't go easy on him.

654
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:12,299
If he dares to make you angry,

655
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,900
just slap him across the face.

656
00:21:15,039 --> 00:21:17,180
Why would I hit my own child?

657
00:21:17,539 --> 00:21:19,859
Can't you wish us well?

658
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:23,220
Look at what you're saying.

659
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:25,500
How do I not wish you well?

660
00:21:26,079 --> 00:21:26,980
If nothing else,

661
00:21:27,259 --> 00:21:28,839
as soon as I heard you were remarrying,

662
00:21:28,980 --> 00:21:30,579
I immediately discussed it with Dabao.

663
00:21:30,740 --> 00:21:31,980
To see for you,

664
00:21:32,079 --> 00:21:33,799
what dowry to prepare.

665
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:34,599
Saying what?

666
00:21:34,599 --> 00:21:35,000
Saying...

667
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:35,680
What are you saying?

668
00:21:35,680 --> 00:21:37,000
What kind of dowry?

669
00:21:37,059 --> 00:21:38,059
Exactly.

670
00:21:38,079 --> 00:21:39,539
No rush on the dowry.

671
00:21:39,740 --> 00:21:42,059
Mom needs to take wedding photos first.

672
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,099
And get a pre-marital checkup.

673
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,640
What are you saying?

674
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:46,200
What checkup?

675
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:47,480
Look how old I am.

676
00:21:47,539 --> 00:21:48,900
For healthy reproduction.

677
00:21:50,079 --> 00:21:51,440
You don't need that anymore, right?

678
00:21:52,839 --> 00:21:53,539
Anyway,

679
00:21:53,599 --> 00:21:54,640
what we mean is,

680
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,400
we firmly support you.

681
00:21:56,839 --> 00:21:58,740
Before, we weren't good.

682
00:21:58,740 --> 00:21:59,059
Not good.

683
00:21:59,059 --> 00:22:00,519
We didn't do right.

684
00:22:00,519 --> 00:22:01,279
We didn't do right.

685
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:02,160
From now on,

686
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:03,980
we'll definitely visit you often.

687
00:22:04,859 --> 00:22:06,779
Bringing your grandson Doudou.

688
00:22:06,779 --> 00:22:07,180
Dou...

689
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:10,420
If...

690
00:22:10,819 --> 00:22:12,079
it can really be like that,

691
00:22:13,099 --> 00:22:14,880
I wouldn't need to remarry.

692
00:22:15,180 --> 00:22:15,920
Don't.

693
00:22:15,920 --> 00:22:17,400
Don't back out!

694
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,240
I've already spoken to my "dad,"

695
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:21,960
that Professor Fan,

696
00:22:22,099 --> 00:22:24,140
we've had a chat.

697
00:22:24,640 --> 00:22:26,039
His conditions,

698
00:22:26,119 --> 00:22:27,859
are seriously good.

699
00:22:28,380 --> 00:22:30,579
Has money, a house, and a car.

700
00:22:30,819 --> 00:22:33,019
No kids, no wife.

701
00:22:33,180 --> 00:22:34,160
Has everything he should have.

702
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:35,619
Lacks everything he should lack.

703
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:38,700
I reckon in a few years,

704
00:22:38,779 --> 00:22:40,980
you can take over.

705
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:43,299
In short,

706
00:22:43,380 --> 00:22:45,200
we firmly support you.

707
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:45,839
Support you.

708
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:47,740
You mean to say,

709
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,660
I outlive him,

710
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:51,940
and you can plot for his property?

711
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:53,839
No, not that... put it this way,

712
00:22:54,079 --> 00:22:55,880
Natural attrition.

713
00:22:56,460 --> 00:22:57,220
Rest assured,

714
00:22:57,960 --> 00:22:59,519
he'll definitely go before you.

715
00:23:02,859 --> 00:23:05,779
I don't need children like you visiting me.

716
00:23:06,599 --> 00:23:07,339
Get out.
